{
  "texts": [
    "The two most popular forms of support for instructors and researchers across disciplines were: 1) self-directed learning from online sources, and 2) learning from peers in their field, in formal or informal formats.",
    "When it came to self-directed learning, many interviewees turned to the web, as one associate professor in law described, \"I've used the internet to teach me.\"",
    "YouTube tutorials were a popular source of information about generative AI, as were internet forums and social media.",
    "Some interviewees were relying on online modules offered by other organizations or tech companies or had simply scoured the internet for resources in varied locations.",
    "Interviewees had high satisfaction with this type of self-directed learning because it allowed them to find resources tailored to their specific needs and do so on their own time."
  ]
}